cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless information-centric networks and their caching mechanisms, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the throughput capacity and latency in information-centric networks, which are fundamental limits that can be analyzed using information theory. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The caching mechanism in information-centric networks involves distributed storage and retrieval of data, which falls under the domain of distributed computing. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses content discovery mechanisms in information-centric networks, which can be analyzed using social and information network models. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper analyzes the performance of information-centric networks in terms of throughput capacity and latency, which falls under the domain of performance analysis.
